<Link id="l00569" /><CodeLine lineNumber="569"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="570"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Compute the order in which we serialize Frames.  The order does not matter</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="571"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in terms of correctness, but we still compute it for deserialization</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="572"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// performance.  Specifically, if we serialize frequently used Frames one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// after another, we have better cache utilization.  For two Frames that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// appear equally frequently, we break a tie by serializing the one that tends</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="575"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to appear earlier in call stacks.  We implement the tie-breaking mechanism</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="576"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// by computing the sum of indexes within call stacks for each Frame.  If we</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="577"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// still have a tie, then we just resort to compare two FrameIds, which is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// just for stability of output.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><span class="doxyHighlight">  std::vector&lt;std::pair&lt;memprof::FrameId, const memprof::Frame &#42;&gt;&gt; FrameIdOrder;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><span class="doxyHighlight">  FrameIdOrder.reserve(MemProfFrameData.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mapvector/#acf4c09e1f30cdd4e0b5b1b8a236ead34">size</a>());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;&#91;Id, Frame&#93; : MemProfFrameData)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><span class="doxyHighlight">    FrameIdOrder.emplace&#95;back(Id, &amp;Frame);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(MemProfFrameData.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mapvector/#acf4c09e1f30cdd4e0b5b1b8a236ead34">size</a>() == FrameIdOrder.size());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a74cdbd1e4f731e7d7cd83461b8b1de0b">llvm::sort</a>(FrameIdOrder,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><span class="doxyHighlight">             &#91;&amp;&#93;(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::pair&lt;memprof::FrameId, const memprof::Frame &#42;&gt; &amp;L,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><span class="doxyHighlight">                 </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::pair&lt;memprof::FrameId, const memprof::Frame &#42;&gt; &amp;R) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;SL = FrameHistogram&#91;L.first&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;SR = FrameHistogram&#91;R.first&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Popular FrameIds should come first.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (SL.Count != SR.Count)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><span class="doxyHighlight">                 </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> SL.Count &gt; SR.Count;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If they are equally popular, then the one that tends to appear</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// earlier in call stacks should come first.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (SL.PositionSum != SR.PositionSum)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><span class="doxyHighlight">                 </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> SL.PositionSum &lt; SR.PositionSum;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Compare their FrameIds for sort stability.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlight">               </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> L.first &lt; R.first;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><span class="doxyHighlight">             &#125;);</span></CodeLine>
